3) Why I reject the other CD: I am not rejecting Carly Simon's greatest-hits collection on quality grounds—it's a respected, popular compilation with strong songwriting and memorable tracks. However, given my role as a CD enthusiast who values the listening experience a physical disc can highlight (dynamic instrumentation, iconic rock tones, and replayable, high-energy tracks), Steppenwolf's All Time Greatest Hits better aligns with those priorities. Its classic-rock catalog offers more of the immediate, sonically engaging material that tends to shine in focused CD listening sessions, whereas the Carly Simon compilation, while excellent, provides a softer, more introspective pop/adult-contemporary experience that is less aligned with the specific listening attributes I prioritized.

